<br>
As far as items which can be clicked from inventory goes, it's nice but doesn't make a lot of sense really.  As much as I love clicking my Tboots from inventory, you wouldn't hear me crying if I had to &lt;gasp&gt; swap them into my armour slots to activate them.  It's already the case with our illusion masks and only seems fair that if there's to be a benefit from the item, that we make a sacrifice of time/main inventory/effort/whatever in order to get that benefit.  With items as powerful as primal procs, that would be just overpowering to let them be clicked from inventory. <p><center><span style="font-variant: small-caps; font-weight: 700; background-color: #FFFF00">
